In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients, except the pandan leaves, together and rub the marinade into the meat. Refrigerate for 1 hour.Meanwhile, rinse the rice until the water runs clear and then cook to packet instructions.Fill a glass bowl with boiling water and soak the pandan leaves for 1 minute to make them more pliable.Wrap each chicken thigh in a leaf, securing tightly with a cocktail stick.Heat a large wok over a medium heat with a dash oil. Fry the parcels for 6â€“8 minutes on each side, or until cooked through.Serve alongside the jasmine rice.